register.description: Voltage domain 0 event and control set register.

bitfield.description: In this field we select which of the event contributions of the 8-maximum possible temp-monitors controlled by this VTM will contribute to generate the merged event/alerts of this VD0.

If this bit is set then the LT_TH0_alert will only become ‘0’ when all its contribution alerts from the multiple sensors selected are all ‘0’.

register.description: Voltage domain 6 VID actual code used as reference by Firmware to set the various voltage domain supply voltages. Reset defaults are sourced from efuse for each OPP.

bitfield.description: VID code that represents the required VDD value in this Voltage domain to operate at OPP_TRB (turbo).

VID code that represents the required VDD value in this Voltage domain to operate at OPP_LOW.
